deck_excerpt: Cyber Dragon OTK deck to break meta Gameplay of the deck : https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=iDCUwNmW1nI&feature=youtu.be
deck_description: Gameplay of the deck : https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=iDCUwNmW1nI&feature=youtu.be     Pure Cyber Dragon is an OTK deck that emphasizes the potential of powerfull attackers like Chimeratech Rampage Dragon to easily deal more than the 8000 needed damages. Here we play techs to ensure spam to get access to a solid offensive board, and struggle against common aggro deck weaknesses like consistant backrows.   So the monster engine countains the better Cyber Dragon monsters to spam the board and add consistancy to our starting hands. The original Cyber Dragon can special summon itsel from the hand if starting second and is the key monster of the loops due to it's name and level 5. Cyber Dragon Core is an amazing starter that sports the name Cyber Dragon on the field and in the graveyard like it's comrades to enable tuto spells to trigger easily, and can tuto a Cyber Dragon spell/trap when normal summoned to gain access to all our combos. It can restart boards in case of a non-successfull first turn by banishing itsel from the graveyard to special summon from the deck. Cyber Dragon Herz is the better discard target of the deck, since it can search or recycle a Cyber Dragon to keep our ressources up, and can more occasionnaly become level 5 when special summoned. Cyber Dragon Nachster pairs perfectly with Herz by discarding a monster to special summon itself then special summon a machine with 2100 Atk or Def from the graveyard, meaning Cyber Dragon and most of the extra deck. Lastly Galaxy Soldier is usefull to summon xyz 5 monsters and is a free extra deck summon paired with Herz effect, and Jizukiru, The Star Destroying Kaiju will be a searchable tech to bypass Dangerous monsters with great stats/protection effect/disruption effect. Ash Blossom soften the going second match ups by negating a tuto and so restrainig the opponent's board.   The spell and traps package is designed to develop the spam potential and ensure OTKs. Cyber Emergency and Cyber Repair Plant are must have cards that trigger a tuto effect to search all monsters of the deck and instantly gain access to starters/extenders/kaiju. Cyber Revsystem acts like a rebirn for Cyber Dragon and will be usefull to finish a board by summoning Cyber Dragon Sieger on a Qliphort Genius. Lastly Machine Duplication is an amazing extender that will automatically summon 2 Cyber Dragon from the deck since the little Cyber Dragon monsters gains the name "Cyber Dragon" on the field, we have a free link summon or xyz 5 summon. To add consistancy we play Pot Of Desires to draw 2 cards almost freely and gain numerous options to better OTK. One For One will summon a monster by discarding another, so it can create card advantage thanks to Herz and enable explosive starts. To fusion summon Cyber Dragons, Overload Fusion will banish monsters from the graveyard to fusion summon and wil pair well with Cyberload Fusion that can use banished monsters, these two cards consisting on a great OTK potential when played together. To add defense we have Called By The Grave that protects our starters from monster hand traps, and Twin Twisters to break through backrows and take down fatal floodgates like There Can Be Only One or Monarch Erupt/Skill Drain.   To absorb the countereffect of Cyber Dragon Nachster, the extra deck countains 14 machine monsters. Qliphort Genius can pressure a negate on the field and free 2 extra zones to assemble great boards. Cyber Dragon Sieger can give 2100 Atk to a Cyber Dragon monster to gain access to powerfull OTKs and protect key monsters from opponent's battlephases. Chimeratech Megafleet Dragon acts like a pseudo kaiju to break powerfull monsters placed in the extra zone like Apollousa to build your boards more easily. Chimeratech Fortress Dragon can be used as a beatstick in critical situations, but most notably fuse the opponent's board, being a threat for decks like Orcusts and other Cyber Dragons. Chimeratech Rampage Dragon is the main offensive threat, it breaks backrow and gain access to 3 attacks by discarding key monsters from the deck like Herz and Core being a triple 4200 Atk monster thanks to Sieger. Cyber Twin Dragon is an alternative to Otk with a potential 4900 dual attack. Cyber Dragon Nova is easy to summon and can revive a Cyber Dragon plus boost one of it's comrades, he is equally the slap target of Cyber Dragon Infinity that absorb attack position monsters and give a great neagtion effect to the board to protect OTKs and pressure opponent's turns. Lastly Constellar Pleiades is an alternative before using Nachster effect to bounce cards and disrupt opponent's board, and Salamangreat Almiraj is a fair way to have a monster in the graveyard to trigger Cyber Repair Plant and protect an Infinity when starting first.

deck_description: Dark magicain's robe is used at 3 in the deck to be able to bring out a dark magician turn 1, and that + plus circle leading to an easy removal of something that might already be causing you problems With Rod you would want to either pick Dark Magic Circle, Magician's navigation, or Eternal soul. Eternal soul and Magician's navigation is more for if you already have a Dark Magician in hand and a Dark Magical Circle on the field. Apprentice Illusion Magician can be ran at either 2 or 3, its at 3 though because of Magician's naviagtion and spellbook of knowledge spellbook of Knowledge can also be ran at 2 or 3, or even 1 as its more of a situational card, but 2 would be best for the deck Inari Fire is at 2 for the link material, though you can only control 1 it makes for a good turn 1 summon, and even as a defence if you need it Curtian is in there as a free summon + circle, but can be used as apprentice discard for cost Illusion Magic works well with a Magican's navigation, or a Eternal soul. Best used with Circle on field The Extra deck is a BIT random, mainly the link monsters but you can switch out some of the Xyz monsters for another Ebon Illusion or Ebon High. Normally with The Eye Of Timaeus you want to go into Dark Magican the dragon knight, to protect your backrow and as a free removal with Dark Magical Circle Magician of dark illusion is a good combo with the traps or even a quick-play, as long as it isnt during the damage step. you can summon it in defence position to protect your lifepoints and banish a card if you have Magic Circle on the field

Skilldrain is an awesome card, because you don't need most of your effects on the field, because the Tenyi trigger in the GY or hand. The Blue Eyes Ultimate is just for Fists of the Unrivaled Tenyi. Waterfall of the Dragons, is your best draw card. Just throw up on of your Tenyi and draw 2 cards. Lost wind  is just one of my favourite current cards. It's awesome for going first, and very often saves your ass.     Avramax and Unicorn are actually cards I use very rarely. They can probably go out for something different. They were just inside because of the scapegoat combo, wich comes also very rarely in this deck. Maybe a Borreload Savage Dragon would be an good option, but he's to expensive for me. By the way, this deck is very cheap.

deck_excerpt: Endymion deck that has high OTK potential and fast board build speed that can make a board hard to break.
deck_description: An Endymion deck that wants to go second. This deck has a high OTK potential while testing the deck I went 10-0 thanks to building big boards easily and people not really knowing what to do against Magister (at least the people I went against). A combo I found useful was to use the effect of Supreme King Dragon Darkwurm from the grave or normal summon to get a Supreme King Gate Zero from the deck. Then placing the Gate in the pendulum zone along with Servant, Chronograph, or Endymion. You can use the effect of Chronograph in the Pendulum Zone to special summon Timegazer to the field and replace the Chronograph with any other pendulum you want and then special summon with the Pendulum Zones. You can then summon Electrumite and use its effect to discard then to discard and add to hand. The second effect should be Master Cerberus or Endymion and then add them back to your hand. You can then Pendulum summon to swarm the field and summon Borrelsword and use its effect so it can attack twice which should be enough to finish off your opponent.

Go with the Flow....

A deck where every monster is recyclable and can be reused over and over to out last your opponent or to over whelm. By using the effects of cards like Gimmick puppet dreary doll to banish gimmick puppets from the graveyard or newer monster to the gimmick puppet archetype like bisque doll and terror baby you can use these in tandem with the effects of the orcust monsters to shuffle back into the deck to reset plays and use the multiple effects of they're link monsters without needing to banish exclusively orcust monsters. By doing this you can summon dreary doll from the GY and then shuffle the banished gimmick puppet back into the main or extra deck to get the effect of the orcust link. The gimmick puppet link can also still use its search effect and not completely lock out orcust from the extra deck with their xyz dingrisu still being summonable.  The Gimmick puppets also allow for cards such as trade-in and machine duplication to be ran in the main deck for quicker deck thinning and easy link climbing through using dreary doll or orcust knightmare as machine duplication targets and draw power with dreary dolls, bisque doll and world wand all being trade-in targets. Gimmick puppets also allow for orucst to make use of cards such Condolence puppet to put at the minimum 1 gimmick puppet in the GY and then to ability to make XYZ's monsters immune to destruction such as dingirsu but to also run Rank-magic cards in the main deck such as rank-up magic numeron force which can be used on dingirsu to go into either of the gimmick puppet CXYZ's monsters and negate all other face-up cards on the field in the process.

deck_name: Shaddoll Artifact Invoked October 2019 post banlist
deck_excerpt: Control oriented Shaddoll build that takes advantage of the resurgence of El Shaddoll Construct Gameplay of the deck : https://www.youtube.com/watch?
deck_description: Gameplay of the deck : https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6g8FADN0wLI&feature=youtu.be     So today let's try a deck using El Shaddoll Construct since it came back to 3. Shaddoll engine is usable in a fair amount of decks, here we go with a combination of 4 engines that can lock the opponent or just OTK with Artifacts, Invokeds and Mekk-Knights. So the strategy is to set a board using the combo with Mekk-Knight of The Morning Star to countain opponent's monster effects and back it up with Invoked monsters like Mechaba and Artifacts like Scythe if having Artifact Sanctum or a way to summon Artifacts from the graveyard. When going second, the idea is to abuse of Mekk-Knight engine and Shaddoll Fusion's full power effect to set a solid OTK board that can bypass most of boards when having sufficient ressources.   So the monster engines are quite specific due to the presence of 4 archetypes. The shaddoll engine countains Shaddoll Beast, Shaddoll Dragon and Shaddoll Hedgehog to respectively draw, destroy backrow and tuto other shaddoll cards when sent to the graveyard by a card effect, meaning that you can use Shaddoll Fusion at his full potential when going second, and even Invocation if not having the Shaddoll Fusion. It is usefull to create card advantage while setting the basics of your boards, or just contribute to lock the opponent when finishing a going first turn with El Shaddoll Winda and El Shaddoll Grysta. The artifacts are reduced to 2 Artifact Scythe and Artifact Moralltach to avoid bricks but have fair chances to have one paired with Artifact Ignition. They special summon themselves when destroyed from the spell and trap zones and trigger an effect if it was during the opponent's turn, the first one locking the extra deck and the second destroying a card on the field. They contribute to countain opponent's board when starting first to better OTK and are materials for the summon of El Construct Shaddoll and Invoked Mechaba. Be aware that since they set themselves in the backrow, they can help the summon f the Mekk-Knight monsters so you can spam more easily. Invoked engine of course is reduced to Aleister The Invoker, and gains power thanks to Salamangreat Almiraj that can use the normal summoned Aleister to directly enable the summon of Mekk-Knight monsters when going first and have an Aleister in the graveyard to fully use Invocation. They also can give a +1000/1000 boost for any fusion monster to survive some battle phases or perform  OTKs with offensive threats like Invoked Purgatrio. Finally the Mekk-Knight engine goes for 3 Mekk-Knight Purple Nightfall, 2 Mekk-knight Blue Sky, 1 Mekk-Knight Indigo Eclipse and 1 Mekk-Knight Red Moon. Purple can tuto by banishing himself or another Mekk-Knight, meaning that you will be ensured to have an Invoked Mechaba when going first, and a monster that will come back for the next turn to search Blue and spam the board. Blue Sky tuto an equal amount of cards that are in the opponent's side of it's column to search the entire engine and rapidly get access to threats like Borrelsword Dragon. Indigo moves the Mekk-Knight to liberate zones for more summons and is the master piece of the control combo of going first games. Lastly Red can destroy monsters of the same column by banishing a Mekk-Knight of the graveyard and can enable OTKs by cutting annoying monsters in defense position or with some defensive effects.   The spell and traps packages is designed to soften the statistics and enabling the most spam potential for defensive first turns or offensive second turns. The invoked engine countains 3 Magical Meltdown to protect monster effects and tuto Aleister, and Invocation to summon Invoked fusion monsters using Aleister from the graveyard and some monsters in opponent's graveyard to limitate some decks like Cyber Dragon by striking key monsters. Invocation can come back in the deck from the graveyard to recycle banished Aleisters and generate defensive plays or more spam plays. Lastly The Book Of The Law can fusion simmon an Invoked monster by using another on the field in rapid effect to protect your monsters from destruction or extend battle phases to gain access to easier OTKs. The Artifact engine countains 2 Artifact Ignition and 3 Artifact Sanctum. Ignition can destroy a spell or trap card in rapid effect to set an artifact in the backrow zones directly from the deck and cycle it, this is usefull to suppress annoying cards of the opponent or just trigger set Artifact monster's effects during the opponent's turn. Artifact Sanctum summons an Artifact monster directly from the deck and can search Scythe to lock the extra deck and punish a lot of meta decks or just summon a Moralltach to destroy a card in specific match ups like Dark Magician and True Draco to catch an Eternal Soul or a Dragonic Diagram World Legacy Cards allows more consistancy. World Legacy Succession reborns a monster in a link zone to abuse of fusion monsters effects or spam the board, and World Legacy's Secret can lock some decks when going first thanks to it's ability to be searched out by Mekk-Knight of The Morning Star to negate several monsters effect in combination with Mekk-Knight Indigo Eclipse or just reborn an Artifact Scythe used for the fusion summon of Invoked Mechaba. Shaddoll fusion is an excellent card for going second match ups since the opponent will almost always ends his turn with an extra deck monster, meaning that you'll be able to fusion summon an El Shaddoll monster using materials directly from the deck to trigger cards like Shaddoll Beast or Shaddoll Dragon to cycle your hand or suppress annoying backrow cards like Monarch Erupt. The El Shaddoll monster will consist on a link material for the summon of Aleister The Invoker Of Madness and will recycle the Shaddoll fusion when sent to the graveyard to gain a free discard target for Invoked Mechaba or Aleister The Invoker Of Madness effects. Lastly to bypass most annoying boards when going second, we use 2 Mind Control And Instant Fusion to steal opponent's monsters and use them as link materials and gain access to higher link monsters more easily or just pressure the opponent's board by forcing out negates.   The extra deck is made to use the full potential of fusion spaming effects with the Aleister The Invoker Of Madness engine. The shaddol engine countains 2 El Shaddoll Construct to maximise the card advantage generated by the Shaddoll Monsters discarded from the deck, 1 El Shaddoll Grysta to pressure boards in specific configurations by striking a special summon, and El Sheddol Winda to restrain the opponent to 1 special summon per turn and completely lock decks in combination with the Artifact engines and monsters like Invoked Mechaba. The Invoked Engine plays Invoked Caliga to start boards with Instant Fusion in case of poor hand when starting first by preparing a target for Invoked Elysium, and can just contribute to fully lock opponent's first turn before setting an OTK. Invoked Mechaba can negate one card per turn and banish it, privating the opponents of destruction effects or secondary effects in the graveyard. Invoked Purgatrio is an axcellent finisher that gains rapidly Atk Following the size of the opponent's board, being a monster that can attack all monsters in the same battle phase with piercing damage. Lastly Invoked Elysium consume more ressources but consists on a formidable weapon against decks like Thunder Dragon by banihing all opponents board with himself or an Invoked monster of the graveyard. Thousand-Eyes Restrict is a target for Instant Fusion when going second, it can steal annoying monsters and beatsticks. By equiping them to itself, it acts like a free starter for the summon of Mekk-Knight monsters. Mekk-Knight of The Morning Star builds consistant board for going first games by setting a board that can negate 2 monster's effects and is hard to bypass by battle. Aleister The Invoker Of Madness is easy to summon thanks to the fair number of different types and attributes of monsters of the deck and acts like a spaming fusion machine for OTK boards. Lastly Borreload dragon is an option to bypass the most resilient monsters and Borrelsword dragon is a good OTK generator if not using the Aleister The Invoker Of Madness combo.     The side deck : Since this deck is already consistant when going first, the biggest part of the extra deck is designed to soften going second match ups. Nibiru, the primal being is a Deadly weapon against combo decks like Guardragons that will able solid otks and add a free material for the summon of Aleister The Invoker Of Madness on our board. Twin Twisters is a good way of Breaking backrow cards that can be annoying if there are too much stacked. It can also discard some cards like the Shaddoll monsters to generate a little card advantage. A third Mind Control will be usefull against decks like Thuder Dragon that runs Colossus, a threat that lock effects of key cards like Aleister The Invoker. Artifact Lancea is a searchable card to disable decks like Orcust, and can be used as fusion material for Invoked Mechaba and El Shaddoll Artifact. Super Polymerization and Starving Venom Fusion Dragon can stop decks by suppressing 2 key monsters of a loop and generate a beatstick that will enable quick summoning of Aleister The Invoker Of Madness next turn. Lastly Anti-Spell Fragrance and Imperial Order could seem couterproductive, but if starting first they can completely shut down Pendulums and Sky Strikers, specially in combination with our first turn board. In the worst cases, they can be used as cost for our monsters effects.

Adrian Gecko, known in the Japanese version as Amon Garam, is a student hailing from East Academy who enters Duel Academy in the third year. Reserved and secretive, Adrian is a neutral character whose actions seem to only serve the Gecko Family and himself. However, after obtaining the spirit of "Exodia the Forbidden One" in the third alternate dimension, he intends to rule it as a world where darkness, and evil will vanish. He thus acts as a secondary antagonist towards Jaden and the primary antagonist, Yubel.

Jim "Crocodile" Cook was a transfer student from South Academy. He used a Fossil Fusion Deck, showcasing his love of geology and archaeology. Wherever you found Jim, you would also find Shirley - his pet crocodile that he carried on his back. When Jim and his friends were trapped in another dimension, he used his Eye of Orichalcum - a mystic item that saw the good and evil inside a person to uncover the darkness within Jaden's heart. Though he tried to defeat the Supreme King, he ultimately failed, so he entrusted Axel to save Jaden. After returning to Earth, he went back to South Academy.

deck_excerpt: PURE Raidraptor Build for CONSISTENT Ultimate Falcon
deck_description:
This is a competitive build for Raidraptors during the Salamangreat format and features multiple ways to bring out Raidraptor - Ultimate Falcon and several other win conditions including Darkest Diabolos, Lord of the Lair and Number 77: The Seven Sinswhile taking budget into consideration. To OTK:
  1. Summon Raidraptor - Ultimate Falcon using Magic Rank-up Skip Force
  2. On your next turn, detach a material from Ultimate Falcon so opponent cannot respond
  3. Summon two raidraptor monsters (e.g. tribute lanius -> dump mimicry -> special pain lanius)
  4. Special summon Wee Witch's Apprentice w/ Ultimate Falcon and pain lanius (lowest ATK)
  5. Activate Skip Force to revive Ultimate Falcon
  6. Overlay into Number 77: The Seven Sins
Note: More resources may be necessary if the opponent has many monsters Different ways to special summon Diabolos:
  1. Tribute a Raidraptor monster or D.D. Crow with Swallow's Nest
  2. Tribute a Raidraptor monster or D.D. Crow with Underclock Taker
  3. Activate Raidraptor Last Strix's effect to tribute itself
The combos played out with this deck can be seen on this Youtube Channel: https://youtu.be/PI9Re_Nkm-U I plan to update this deck every month with combo videos each time.

deck_excerpt: Souleating Ovirapter is your key card, use fossil dig to add it or whatever. The rest of the combo is yours if no negations come from your opponent.
deck_description: Souleating Oviraptor is your key. Add it using Fossil Dig if you do not have it.  Summon it, then send carbonedden to the GY, banish carbon to SS flamvell guard, then those 2 sync into IB, then IB adds qorld legacy guardragon.  Activ world legacy guardragon, SS flamvell from gy, then link Ib and Flamvell into Beat cop to the right zone (it des not really matter, but there is a change here ***). IB SS World CHALICE Guardragon, then use it to link into elpy to the rightmost(*** If you summoned Beat Cop to the left Link Zone, then Summon Elpy to the LEFTMOST zone, not rightmost) zone.  Then banish chalice dragon from gy to SS Flamvell, then link into Pisty to the middle. Then elpy's eff to SS Brotuar, Brotaur's eff, adding chaos drag levieneer.  The rest is not set. Meaning, whatever you have in your hand, go with it. Go to youtube and watch some vids on "Dragon deck OCT 2019" if you need more help. But you should end up with at least 2 or more LOCKDOWN monsters (Hope Harbringer, Dawn dragster, Savage, apollosa, etc)  The Sauravaris is just incase opponent uses Impermanence or Effect Veiler, Called by the Grave is self explanatory (stops ash, effect veiler, ghost ogre etc), Red-Eyes is just in case you DRAW into Brotaur for your draw phase at the start of the duel, in which case, you need to go for the Original Guardragon Crusadia combo.

Been testing this deck on the Dueling Nexus. Granted not the most reliable, but very helpful online dueling site. Have had a high success rate for the deck. Gearing up for the next local tournament I attend. Nibiru obviously is a worry, but Rafale can stop it. Mind Control is amazing in the deck. For example you open with 2 fur hire monsters and need a 3rd type to go into folgo. Well mind control takes care of that. deck_description: The primary goal of the deck is to end on more than just a Unchained Soul of Rage. I like to strive for Unchained Soul, to link with an opponents monster, which then points to one level 8 D/D/D monster, whether that's Beowulf to blow up spells and traps during my next turn, or Siegfried for a negate. Depending on the hand you could end with even better. This deck gains more and more with each turn that goes by. The deck has three key search cards, being Abomination's Prison, Dark Contract with the Gate, and Dark Spirit's Mastery (can search Unchained Soul of Disaster, and Oblivion King).

deck_description: fusion
phantom knights,red eyes, odd eyes mix.

Started out trying to make a deck around the Draconia cards. Then it turned into a pet project of mine. I’ve fine tuned it and it performed well at locals, obviously it struggled against the top decks like Salamangreats and Orcust but all in all I feel like it did well for it just being a casual deck.  Basically you want to see Rescue Rabbit turn one. If you don’t; Unexpected Dai works as a backdoor opener. Both is even better. You want to do some Electrumite plays, usually targeting Hallohallo, for some synchro plays. If your going first, you want to end with a Apollousa, Dawn Dragster, and Borreload Savage ideally. Sometimes all it can muster is two of the three, which is fine.  If you are going second, which is better with this deck imo, you want to use the Utopia Double package for big damage. Also you could work in a level 8 synchro to augment what little life points your opponent would have left. Otherwise you can cheese number 82 for game.  I like this deck a lot, it really have the versatility to deal with just about any situation. Which is why I side Black-Winged dragon for the occasional burn deck. Obviously it’s not a top tier deck, and it bricks if you draw all vanillas or the “garnet” double or nothing. I’ve experimented with the side cards for a more control based strategy but it’s even more inconsistent. I tried out some Igknights and even took royal magical library for a spin, no dice. If you guys have any suggestions I’d love to hear them. This deck has become my side Yugioh project and I’d love to somehow make it more viable than my Altergeist deck. Which is doubtful but I’m having fun with it.

deck_description: This is a deck for my coworker for ygopro

Simple deck strategy of using both the fire king and nephthys engines together to continuously destroy your own cards and your opponents over and over by making use of the fire king lock using 2 Garunix's and a sacred phoenix of nephthys to continuously destroy themselves wiping out everything on the field. Other options the deck can go into is making use of the nephthys link 3 monster to create an indestructible beatstick which can remain on the field indefinitely and can be used as cost for some of the monsters effects in the deck such as fire king ganesha and cerulean sacred phoenix of nephthys. One last major late game option is link climbing using rekindling on the decks fire kings to easily go into the link 4's of the deck, namely topologic bomber dragon to once again nuke the field continuously. deck_excerpt: Attention all Red-eyes Players, i think i have made a break through
deck_description: Sup guys. I know that the latest red-eyes support as come out so i decided to try and make a deck out of the new card since it is really good and i mean REALLY good! This is the deck that i found the most success with in terms of making this a pure red-eyes build and i must say the deck actually does pretty well against other decks. the idea for this is to either go first or second(it doesn't really matter but first is prefered) and essentially create a board full of interruptions that your opponent will be forced to play through. normal you do have ask blossom or some kind of hand that will allow you to negate your opponents effects. the deck is not necessarily suppose to stop your opponent rather slow it down so the deck can keep up with your opponents speed. as i was play testing the deck, it use to be just a slash dragon pass deck and maybe with fang with chain on the board. this deck does a similar thing except you summon "Dragun of Red-eyes" and then set a trap or two. those traps usually being fang with chain or some other disruption card. yes i know you cant target dragun, but even then your end result should still have at least one or two disruptions since you also have a chance of having ash blossom in your hand as well. pot of desires and allure of darkness are also there to boost the consistency since red-eyes seem to have an issue with it as well. so now the question is, what so i think about the deck so far? well to bee honest the new support is absolutely amazing and is a good first turn board not only providing a big beater for your opponent to get over but also a disruption as well. i think the deck is decent at best. of course the deck is not meta by any means but i do know that this is defiantly a step in the right direction for red-eyes since the deck itself hasn't been getting the respect it deserves. yes the card line up does seem a little awkward, but that doesn't mean it cant be make good by any stretch of the imagination. if you guys have any ideas on what to put in to make this beck better, feel free to comment down below.

deck_excerpt: D/Ds are a going first powerhouse yet again thx to Clotheep
deck_description:
Video: https://youtu.be/y7hldMAAVG0 Card Ratio explanations: 
  • 3x D/D/D Oblivion King Abyss Ragnarok - Literally none runs less, there are 0 reasons to run less amazing card
  • 3x D/D Vice Typhoon - Probably the worst of the amazing combo pieces, you can often side the 3rd for extra deck techs. You want to see as much combo pieces as possible so I really don't want to run less then 3
  • 3x D/D Savant Copernicus - I have seen people run less then 3. THOSE HAVE 0 IDEA what the fk they are doing with D/Ds period. This card is literally an Arma knight of the deck with 5 amazing targets. How MENTAL do you have to be to run less.
  • 1x D/D Savant Thomas - This card is not an amazing combo piece but it is a combo piece, Usually it is a combo piece for late parts of a combo. I have seen people run more, maybe they don't want to banish it off desires but it ll just brick your hands. RUN 1, Laplace is also Thomas 2.0 I would rather run one of each but I am not even doing that. He is far from a bad card but overated by many. But Maybe I am biased as a Croatian and Tesla fan (No I am not)
  • 3x D/D Swirl Slime - Everyone runs 3. The best combo piece. This card was semi-limited at one point that says enough
  • 3x D/D Necro Slime - I could understand people running less then 3 but cards such as Almiraj and Performapal Pop-up really push it to 3.
  • 3x D/D Lamia - Everyone runs 3. Funny enough I often dump all 3 turn 1 (ofc you can only use 1 it just happens with D/D ghost ;P). Used to be semi limited.
  • 1x D/D Ghost - So this card in a nutshell buffs the viability of Necro Slime and Vice Typhoon, because it really fills the graveyard which if you tried playing D/D lately you ll notice is SUPER IMPORTANT. It can also be revived with Clotheep and then you can cross into Fiber since Ghost is a tuner and get Lamia. It works well with most of your combo pieces. I even debated running 2, or running high king Alexander, but it made no sense to go over 40. I went from hating the card to not touching the D/D without it... Ghost wasn't included in some of the replays, I figured running him is optimal via playtesting (An old D/D player)
  • 3x D/D Savant Kepler - Oh yeah... Dark Contract Searcher, so Searches everything. Idk what else to say run 3. Even better in the ocg WITH 2 one for one.
  • 3x Allure of Darkness - Superb card. Here are some card combinations you typically don't want. Kepler + Gate, Necro Slime + Vice Typhoon, Lamia + Copernicus, duplicates.
  • 1x One for one (Unless you are in ocg then run 2) - there are like... 3 good targets duh.
  • 2x Pot of desires - If you banish thomas / Ghost its fine in most of the cases
  • 1x Foolish burial - DUHHHHHHHH
  • 2x Performapal Pop-Up - there are 13 cards you wan't in the graveyard + the deck can always revive everything from the graveyard.. so you can even dump thomas revive him later put up Titanic. Just be careful with life payment. Remind yourself to turn off your own Contracts with Siegfried etc if needed. It ups the consistency of the deck
  • 3x Dark Contract with the Gate - A continous Rota
  • 1x Dark Contract with the Swamp King - this card fusions from both hand field and graveyard. If it fuses from hand / field keep in mind it doesn't banish, it sends your cards to the graveyard so it can sort of act like a Swirl Slimes first effect. I would not fault one for playing 2. Its a great card.
  • 2x Impermanence - so this handtrap can be set.. which is important because you don't want to lose to much lifepoints of performapal Pop-Up
  • 1x Ghost ogre - There is a needlefiber in the deck... this can put Ogre on the field, ogre works from the field. You can also revive ogre with clotheep, since ghost ogre is a tuner you can also link into fiber get lamia
  • 1x Ghost ash - best handtrap in a game by a mile, a tuner.
  Extra deck: 
  • 2x D/D/D Flame King Genghis (Previously known as Temujin) - You literally need 2 for some combos.... Revive
  • D/D/D Flame High King Genghis - I feel like sometimes even the second one is required but there is just nooooo space. Reviver, handles backrow decks well going second
  • D/D/D Oracle King d'Arc- He is just a level 7 fusion you drop which then you use with lamia to enter the Savage / Siegfried. Sometimes he gets revived off your D/D/D revives so that again you can enter something with Lamia. Win condition against burn decks, can save you from Contracts
  • D/D/D Gust King Alexander - D/D reviver, only revives <=4 monsters just like Clotheep
  • Odd-Eyes Meteorburst Dragon - Makes your Ragnarok nutz because at that point Ragnaroks revives twice per turn. Normally such play gives you Titanic
  • D/D/D Cursed King Siegfried- Yes, negates are good, A D/D name so can be revived, can even help you heal a bit of LP
  • Crystal wing Synchro Dragon - OUR CRYSTAL DRAGON IS BACK IN D/D <33333
  • Borreload Savage Dragon - New Addition for D/D decks. Sometimes your ending board is literally 3 level 8 synchros, trust me this isn't to much lvl 8 synchros
  • Desert Locusts - A new card, with Fiber this forces your Opp to discard 1 card. I chose it over Formula, Wonder Magician (don't wanna pop my own contracts), and Shooting Riser Dragon but you can also run any of the 3 without much winrate difference imo.
  • Number 38: Hope Harbinger Dragon Titanic Galaxy - Fk thats a long name, succ the spells, protect the Appolousa..
  • Salamangreat Almiraj- so this helps you put those Lamias, Necro slimes etc in graveyard. It really buffs such cards
  • Apollousa, Bow of the Goddess - Might get banned... This is the only threat for the future of the deck,  this card is also not to essential, other Link4s aren't much worse
  • Crystron Needlefiber - will we ever get him??? Atleast the deck is soon OCG legal with 2 OFA
  • Clotheep - whenever a monster is summoned it does stuff depending on the monster types (synchro, xyz, ritual, fusion) it points to. Overall that normaly means you can revive a monster since it ll point to a fusion. You don't have to use this immedieatly as soon as fusion drops, keep in mind it ll keep pointing to that fusion.
  Side deck
  • Dark Contract with Errors - Ehmm Searchable Royal Decree - Fantastic side going first vs trap decks
  • Dark Contract with The Witch - so this card counters Dark ruler no more. Fantastic side for game 3
  • D/D/D Duo-Dawn King Kali Yuga - I am not maining him as there is no enough space but, he first turn Kali Yuga is win condition against backrow decks. Going second no backrow deck ll let you reach r8 so he just isn't maindeck worthy in my eyes
  • D/D Orthros - Searchable mst with Dark Contract with the Gate
  • 3x Lightning storm - More going second backrow hate
  • 3x Nibiru - some combo hate
  • D/D Evil - side it going first against Pendulums, way to searchable not to be in a side deck since you can always access it when you do..
  • D/D/D Abyss King Gilgamesh - a D/D link... idk he can kinda otk with D/D/D Supreme King Kaiser but going first gameplan is ALIVE AGAIN.
  • D/D/D Wave Oblivion King Ceasar Ragnarok- another long name.. an out to those can not be targeted monsters, but Cwing and Savage can get big to not to mention that Clotheep can boost atk if it points to synchros so you can out those "immunity cards" sort of well already. If you decide to run more Swamps going second strongly consider him. Its a good card space is just tight
  • D/D/D Destiny King Zero Laplace - Ehm Thomas 2.0 in a nutshell, can also out those "immunity monsters" with high attack. So if you face such decks why not have this in a side deck
You can also side virus cards, typical going second handtraps etc, just showing some less conventional options which are super accessible so should be strongly considered for a side deck

deck_excerpt: Draw for deck-out? Why not draw for burn damage? Greed let's you make the latter happen!

I just recently posted a deck on going second muskets because its a deck I really love to play and its so much fun to break your opponent's board and then control the game or kill them right there. Now I want to post my going first list because going first muskets is also a really good deck. The goal is to go first, summon a musket and hopefully be able to have in your opening hand, and use Ties of The Brethren to summon 2 other muskets and pass turn and use musket cards in hand to interrupt your opponent and control the game. There's not very much for me to talk about for this deck because there are not many combos or many details I can talk about. All I can really say is Magical Musketeer Max is broken. The only broken combo in this deck I came up with is that you can use Magical Musketeer Mastermind Zakiel and 2 other monsters to go into the new BLS link 3 and be able to get its effect to become untargetable and indestructible by card effects which is very hard for most decks to get over and most of the time, ends up winning you the game. This deck just got much more powerful since everything else was effected by the banlist but this deck wasn't. I personally believe this version of muskets or the going second build I posted last week is a good meta call for this format. I hope you guys enjoy and stick around for more decks soon, especially post banlist.

deck_excerpt: My personal take on the new and improved HERO archetype, alongside a boss monster for the ages.
deck_description: HEROs are my hands-down favorite archetype, whether it'd be for my love of fast offensive playstyles or seeing the adventures of Jaden Yuki unfold time and time again. And given the support they've gotten this year, nothing made me happier than seeing these bad boys back in style and even crazier than ever. Now, instead of simply one HERO subarchetype reigning a whole deck, all HEROs pop up to make a difference, from all subs and walks of life for one common goal. The idea of the deck is to go for as quick a satisfying KO as possible by quickly summoning low-level Warrior monsters in the form of HEROs, each with their own outstanding effects and potential, to make way for far more powerful Fusion and Link HEROs. It's not necessarily the "mandatory" way to run HEROs, play whatever you want the way you want. It's simply how I personally enjoy running the deck, and you're more than welcome to substitute things for say, Malicious Bane or Infinite Impermanence if your wallet can take it. One thing you'll want to do right away is special summon Vision HERO Faris by discarding a HERO from your hand, preferrably Destiny HERO - Malicious, Elemental HERO Shadow Mist, or any of your Miracle Fusion targets. This, in turn, lets you add Vision HERO Increase to your backrow, which you can then activate to tribute Faris and special summon itself to the field, which then lets you bring Vision HERO Vyon about. Vyon is vital as he allows you to send other grave-centric HEROs there, as well as banish Faris or any other HERO from there to search for Polymerization. Elemental HERO Solid Soldier is vital as both a way to bring out monsters like Stratos and Shadow Mist to the field and a way to recycle HEROs from the grave if it's sent there by a card like Polymerization. Prime targets include the aforementioned Elemental HERO Stratos and Shadow Mist, either for HERO searches, backrow popping, or adding Mask Change to your hand. Destiny HERO - Plasma is also worthwhile given all the extra HEROs on the field you have, being able to take those out to bring itself to the field and let its Skill Drain/Relinquished-esque effects run wild. Onto the Extra deck, Masked HERO Dark Law requires no introduction, as his ability to lock out important grave-centric cards of your opponent and punish them for searching makes him a must for this deck. That's not to say Masked HERO Anki doesn't have his place, though, boasting high ATK and being able to both attack directly and search for additional Mask Changes. Meanwhile, cards like Destiny HERO - Dystopia and Destiny HERO - Dangerous are the reasons to run Fusion Destiny, Dystopia allowing you to do chip damage while Celestial or Decider are in the grave while gaining ATK from either Dread Decimator, Honest Neos, or Dangerous to pop any card your opponent controls, and Dangerous for fodder to send card like Mali and Shadow Mist to the grave. Xtra HERO Cross Crusader acts as a free search if a Destiny HERO's in your grave, meanwhile Xtra HERO Wonder Driver allows you to recycle your Poly's and Mask Changes and Xtra HERO Dread Decimator powers up any HERO it points to. By far the absolute boss monster of the deck is none other than Elemental HERO Sunriser. Requiring generic material to summon, he makes an easy boost to any board of yours, powering up your monsters depending on all the attributes you control and popping a card your opponent controls once a turn when your HERO attacks. Not only that, but he also lets you search Miracle Fusion, helping you set up for Omni-HEROs like Elemental HERO Absolute Zero to act as a ticking time bomb or Elemental HERO Great Tornado for weakening powerful tools. All in all, HEROs make for an optimal OTK tool if played in the right hands, and I sincerely hope you have as much fun with them as I do.

deck_excerpt: One of the most fun and tricky way to play zombies! Enjoy ^_^
deck_description: Well, from some time, I've become a little obsessed about Vendreads. I know that the "Zombie World" would be a better choice, but I wana keep the retro style of the deck (since people are already tired of Doomking  :D  ), so I opted for a 2nd best choice, of mixing the deck with Shiranui. A 100% pure Vendread deck would be to weak, since we all know that the archtype by itself lacks consistency.  Ok, so the main purpose is to have your ritual bad boys armed with aditional effects, but remember, your ritual materials MUST BE ON THE FIELD, for they to receive the best additonal effects. That's why Impcantation (the best support for almost all ritual decks) has no sinergy with this deck, cause you need to you use specific materials. That makes the deck a bit tricky. The most common scene is to have a Revendread Slayer ritual summon by using Revenants and Houndhorde as FIELD materials. In this case you'll have a full armed Slayer with 2 Quick effects that will give opponents headache! ^_^. The best scene is to have an Executor ritual summon using Revenants, Houndhorde and Core as FIELD materials. In this scenario, none of your cards can be targeted by opp effects ;).  And ya, as the main counter we have the frightening rock bastard Nibiru, to punish our opp in case he wants to put to many negations or if he wants to Borrelsword us! If we don't use Nibi in this way, it can be also useful, as he's Lv 11, and can be used as entire tribute from hand for all the ritual monsters.  Enough with the words! If you guys enjoy the deck, go play it, and never forget to have fun! ^_^

deck_name: Saved by the Yubel (E-HERO Neos Kluger)
deck_excerpt: My take on the upcoming Neos Kluger, alongside several options to help get the most out of it using HEROs and Neo-Spacians.
deck_description: The gist of the deck is to try and overwhelm your opponent with Neos Fusion monsters, typically Elemental HERO Neos Kluger, who boasts an effect that deals effect damage equal to monsters it battles and a free Neos Wiseman upon destruction, as well as Rainbow Neos that allows for clutch resets depending on which effect of his you activate. Several other HEROs make an appearance, such as Elemental HERO Shadow Mist and Vision HERO Vyon. You'll want to try and discard Shadow Mist using the effects of either Vision HERO Faris, Predaplant Ophrys Scorpio, Neo-Spacian Aqua Dolphin, Super Polymerization, or send it to the grave by the effect of Vyon or Neos Fusion. Once done so, she lets you search a HERO from your deck, and you'll most likely wanna go for Elemental HERO Honest Neos to power up your other HEROs. Elemental HERO Brave Neos also pops up in the Extra Deck, letting you search any Neos-supporting card after destroying an opponent's monster and powering up from any Neo-Spacian or HERO in your grave. Elemental HERO Grand Neos, meanwhile, lets you get rid of your opponent's tools without having to worry about certain ones with non-destruction or graveyard effects. Elemental HERO Divine Neos was kinda added in as an "if all else fails" option, and figured would help since Elemental HERO Sunriser and Predaplant Verte Anaconda can both help get those effects off.

deck_name: Fluffal - Clotheep, Anaconda, Dragun of Red-eyes
deck_excerpt: Fluffies can actually go first with this support. They can put up to 3 Negates. That is a welcome addition to a deck which already strives going secon
deck_description:
https://youtu.be/FMVsDHepZWM - Deck in action on youtube (Subscribe perhaps=?) Card Ratio explanations:
  • 3x Fluffal Dog - HOPT On summon searches any other fluffal or edge imp sabres. You want to see him as much as possible
  • 3x Fluffal Bear - Everyone knows about Bear Wings combo. You just have to max out on him
  • 1x Fluffal Penguin - Great card but there is no reason to play more, Muligans your hand (sort of), its board swarm isn't hopt so you can abuse it with Clotheep summoning both Owl &Dog in the same turn. Very good card. Used to be more valuable with Toad and Norder, nowdays just a one off
  • 1x Fluffal Owl - Poly searcher on summon or polymerization itself on the field, can search fusion substitute as can any card which searches poly. Ofc you gotta play 1. By playing 1 any card which searches "Fluffals" also gives a poly access, super relevant if vendor sacks Dog
  • 1x Fluffal Sheep - A must run, allows you to enter Clotheep / Anaconda super easy. Increases the ammount of fusion resources you have by reviving an edge imp and bouncing a fluffal (Dog  / Owl usually), since you can still fuse with monsters in your hand this card indirectly pluses whenever you do that
  • 1x Fluffal Cat - If you fuse with this card you can add back poly. You can Chain mask your key effects such as Frightfur Tiger pop. Not normal summon reliant yet it makes sure you keep fusion summoning which is important for Predaplant Dragostapelia, Sabre Tooth and whatnot
  • 2x Fluffal Wing - Playing 3 is bricky, it works well with performapal - pop up and Dragun of Red-eyes even. If we ever get brill fusion back at 3 I ll play just 1.
  • 3x Edge imp chain - self searcher on attack so another monster which can increase the number of fusion resources. But he is played for the second effect. whenever he is sent to the graveyard from your hand/field by fusion summon, Performapal pop-up, toy vendor.... he can search a frightfur card.. Hi Patchwork
  • 1x Edge imp sabres - Super searchable as both dog, vendor, and frihgtfur patchwork search it. You kinda don't need more then one for your deck to function not that playing 2 would impact your winrate to much. Combos well with Toy Vendor
  • 3x Toy Vendor- So this cards search effect ain't once per turn, somewhat coinflipy but if you do get lucky it puts you so far ahead
  • 1x Performapal Pop-Up - a control able card destruction which doesn't make your opponent draw handtraps. Can be vulnerable to ash but there are quite a few cards you wan't to discard in this deck.
  • 1x Fusion Substitute - As searchable as polymerization is. The draw 1 effect really helps
  • 2x Polymerization - So I am running 2 polymerizations and 1 fusion sub. I recently tried 1-1 ratio, or just 2 polymerization ratio. This is what I prefer just slightly over the other 2 ratios and any other ratio would be trash
  • 1x Frightfur Factory - Continous polymerization altho I kinda don't like this card as I can only fusion Frightfur monsters with it... This card is sort of a must because Edge imp Chain can search it... in case you already cycled patchwork, Frightfur fusion rivals that even less nowdays because it can also be used with Anaconda. One can try running 2x Frightfur fusion instead, but there won't be much winrate diff imo
  • 1x Frightfur fusion - fusion which uses grave and field, searchable and it also works with Anaconda.
  • 3x Foolish burial goods - this is a card you want to draw the most, even more then patchwork. Sends Vendor but you can also send Fusion sub
  • 3x Frightfur Patchwork - better then Pot of Greed in this deck.
  • 1x Red-eyes fusion (Edge imp sabres puts it back in the deck if you draw it)
  • 1x Dark magician  (see above). You need to play him to enter Dragun of Red-eyes off Anaconda which is quite scarry boss monster
  • 1x Phantazmay - Material for Red-eyes fusion I personaly am not a fan of Phantazmay but its the best target
  • 2x Ash
  • 2x Nibiru
  • 2x Storm
Extra deck
  • 2x Frightur Sabre-Tooth - Multiple Sabretooths come up all the time, Don't need 3 due to fusion sub
  • 2x Frightfur Tiger - 2nd Tiger comes up sometimes, its a multi pop card. Sometimes you need multiples
  • 1x Frightfur Wolf - OTK
  • 1x Frightfur Kraken - Kraken + Sabre-Tooth combo can out double colossus
  • 1x Frightfur Sheep - Armades effect, honestly not to relevant but sort of a staple. Don't feel like running Instant fusion for it
  • 1x Frightfur Dare Devil - Both Dark and 8. So can cross into both Felgrand and Dragostapelia.
  • 1x Dragun of Red-eyes - 2 BRICKS are def worth it
  • 1x Divine Dragon Knight Felgrand - Better then other r8s because he can detach for fusion sub. Negate
  • 1x Predaplant Dragostapelia - No we don't summon this with super Poly. Negate
  • 1x Clotheep - Reason why I updated this deck
  • 1x Predaplant verte Anaconda - Reason why I updated this deck
  • 1x Borreload
  • 1x Unicorn - Makes sense to run 1 link 3.
Side deck is standard stuff.

I'm going to assume you know the basics of how a dark magician deck works and just say why and how i use some cards: MAIN DECK Obvious cards no explanation: 3 dark magicians, 3 Magician rod, 3 dark  magical circle 1 dark magic attack Obvious cards with explanation on why this ammount:
*3
apprentice illusions magician: she is core to the deck, helps you search DM and protect them from stronger foes by adding 2k dmg to your monsters, if you have 2 in hand always nice to keep 1 in hand just incase, but making norito could be an other option, situational. some people debate on only using 2 but i say 3 is better since its not a bricky card, it allows you to get your DMs and works very well with navigation. *1 illusion magic: good to search if you have navigation or ethernal sould already, if all your DM are in field or grave but you still have navigation on field and need them in your hand, but mainly because it protects your magician rod from handtraps, hence why some people like to use 2 to increase chances of having it in hand to protect. but i find it very bricky since it's a dead card in many situations. But need 1 minimum *3 magician navigation: another card where people debate to put 3 or 2 but i say 3 is still better since it's effect is so good and works well with illusion aprentice and super poly(if you have no DM on hand, for discard purpose) and it's grave effect is god tear. i will ofter go search for this intead of ethernal soul, unless i have 1 already. 2 ethernal souls: most people use 3 but i rather just have 2 and use dark magic inheritance as a replacement, i find myself wanting more navigation than soul but with inheritance it gives more option. but you can use 3 instead of inheritance. i just find 2 and 1 works better.
Very reccomended but optional:
*2-3 ash blossom& joyous spring with 2-3 called by the grave: i use 3 and 2 of this combo, it's on what you prefer, if you'd rather protect your searches go for grave but if you prefer to stop ememy plays then go ash, but not that impermanece counters grave and ash can only be used once per turn,  depending on situation and first game, i might remove them and switch for side deck on second game *some sort of draw engine, 2 draw engine is optimal. i use 3 pot of duality since most of my special summons happen on oponent turns.specially in the early stages. then i also use the spell book engine, 1 of each because i can't manage to remove other cards to run 1 boy and 2 and 2 books, so i just use one of ea. if you have extravagance, it's also a good option but you would need to modifie the extra deck to have more pairs and at that point may wan to remove a super poly or 2  since you won't be able to relly on it as much. i don't recomend pot of desires since to risky *3 solemn judgment since it counters anything, really strong and destroys all pendulum summon, only counter is supper poly, and onlike strike, if your hp is low, you can still use it. *1 skill drain: if you have this card it's pretty much gg if you have your DM engine on bord.  also if you use magician rod and illusion magic, you can still use rods effect. *3 super poly: saves me so many time, but also a good side deck switch option for when you face things like skystriker since its useless, i'd keep 1 just to posible be able to special summon the dark magician dragon with imduk.
optional card:
dark magic veil: just a solid good card that allows you to summon from graves or hand, works well if illusion apprentice and dark magician if you have circle on feild. magician of dark illusion works well but wouldn't use more than 1
EXTRA DECK good supper poly targets:
*mudragon: for when they don't have dark monsters *starving venom: goto dark super poly target *guardragon almarduke: doesn't happen often but if they ever have 3 link on field, it can break their board. specialy if no dark monsters *predaplant dragostapelia: used if they have a fusion monster and you or him have a dark monster, *dark magician dragon knight: in rare case if they have a dragon, but more often you will use your dark magician with either imduk or whomeever reprodocus is pointing 2.
the 3 xyz monsters are good solid cards to have good link monsters:
* beatcop to protect you ethernal soul, link spider for when you only have 1 darkmagician to circle around with, imduk does the same and is a poly target for you dragon knight but he points to enemy side, so risky sometimes, reproducus for when i only have 1 DM but  multple monster on field so i can turn 1 to dragon and poly with  the DM for dragon knight,(doesn't happen often, mainly use imduk. *black luster soldier  is really good but to expesive for me but if you have it, use it, its really good with you DM since its 7 star. *berserker of tenyi: not that great, but is easy to summon with the trap card fists of the unrivaled tenyi trap card. but if you rather have extra imduk just incase, that works 2
  My side deck this depends on the people deck at you casuals, but i find what i have to be pretty good to counter most decks, i'd say soul drain and summon limit and storming mirrors are very solid picks, and the rest change as you please   the deck is around 150-200$ (not counting black luster soldier) depending on the rarities you go for. the expensive cards are (but not really if you compare other type of deck): apprentice illusion:10-20$ (need 2-3) magician navigation:10-15$ (need 2-3) predaplant triphyovertum:5-10$ ebon illusion:10-20$ (luster if you want it: 70-90$) rest is arroun 1-5$ cards i won't add side deck since thats more situational but other good choice would be nibiru and dinowrestler pankrtops final notes: i tries eye of timaeus but i find it to bricky since you need a DM and you can't search it, you wouldnt want more than 1 or maybe 2 if desperate but it's a dead card, while super poly can be used for multiple different uses. another fun way is to add 2 dragon keeper and trade 1 super poly for 1 ultra poly so you can search. but as fun as it is , its easy to counter, but its fun.

deck_excerpt: Breaking Boards Magical Musketeer Shaddolls (Going Second) (Post October 2019 Banlist)
deck_description: Alright so after this past banlist, I was thinking about the concept of mixing Shaddolls with Magical Muskets since Construct is now back at 3. And after testing this concept on ygopro, the deck I came up with is crazy strong going second and breaks boards really easily. This deck is meant to go second, the way this deck works is that you first use the Muskets to attempt to break their board and you can even use Shaddoll Fusion under the same column as a Musket monster to trigger it's effect and get a strong fusion off. If your first attempt with Muskets fail then you that is why you play 2 Crooked Crown and the Shaddoll engine. Because in this current meta everyone is always ending on an extra deck monster, using Shaddoll Fusion going second is so strong. Since Construct is level 8 as well, you can use Mind Control to take control of your opponent's monster and use another monster you control to go into the new BLS link 3 that is insane and the likely hood of your opponent getting over it is very low unless they are playing Orcust. Also for those of you that are already fans of Magical Musketeers and are wondering why I choose to play 2 Dancing Needle and 2 Crooked Crown its because almost every deck in this format abuses their graveyard and Dancing Needle really hurts, especially against Salad and Orcust. I think for a different format in the future where the graveyard is not as abused Dancing Needle can go to 1 in the deck. The reason for 2 Crooked Crown is because the deck suffers if it loses its normal summon, so you need to be able special summon another Musket monster in order to recover, and the card is a free plus if you activate it under the same column as another Musket monster. I bet you guys are also wondering about Foolish Burial Goods as well. You probably think I'm a madman but in reality this card is broken in this deck. The combo is with Magical Musketeer Doc where you activate Goods under the same column as him and send any Magical Musket Spell or Trap that you want to get back to your hand, and then Doc activates allowing you to add that card from your dump off Goods. This is something I came up with while testing and think its really strong, especially while playing Doc at 3. Also in testing the third Max never comes up for me because the game ends too soon. Even if the third Max comes up in some sort of a long grind game this is why I chose to play 3 Doc and 1 Wild. This deck is also pretty consistent for the most part. deck_excerpt: ABC meta oriented deck Gameplay of the deck : https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bgSm9M8WXnM&feature=youtu.be
deck_description: Gameplay of the deck : https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bgSm9M8WXnM&feature=youtu.be     Here is an ABC deck built to perform against meta with some techs that increase it's stability, defensive abilities and OTK potential. The basics like gadgets and Galaxy Soldier are still here to start the same loops that the classic builds.   So the specific cards you'll find are : The Psy-Frame package, that is usefull to negate an Ash Blossom targetting a draw card or Terraforming/Union Hangar to have 2 monsters to start boards pretty effectively, or just use Psy-Frame Lambda's ability to negate cards during your opponent's turn to add disruption to your established board. Note that they are light attribute and are potential targets for Galaxy Soldier's effect. The Sky Striker package is really good in this deck sinse it can search out multiple Sky Striker cards and cycle the deck when having good effects to handle the opponent's board. Kagari is a machine monster and can be used to summon Platinum Gadget. With Sky Striker Mecha - Shark Canon and Sky Striker Mecha - Widow Anchor you can handle annoying monsters in the graveyard or in the field like Plasma Destiny Hero, and steal opponent's monsters to rapidly gain access to Avramax and Borrelsword for OTK strategies. Monster Gate can deblock hands by sending somme letters to the graveyard that would trigger summoning or searching effects and can bring out monsters like Silver Gadget or Gold Gadget to spam the board and gain access to ABC Dragon Buster even with a bricky hand. Note that you can send spells to the graveyard and instantly gain acces to the full power effects of the Sky Striker cards. Twin Twisters are Added main deck to send a needed letter to the graveyard and break backrow cards and floodgates that could stop the deck in some situations. The extra deck is quite generic, we Simply run a Gear Gigant X to search the last letters for the summoning of ABC Dragon Buster, and Crusadia Equimax to have a simple way to summon Mekk-Knight Crusadia Avramax with the Sky Striker combos or bypass the biggest beatsticks and potentially gain access to simple OTKs.   The side deck : Dark Ruler No More is a great card against combo decks like Guardragons and won't be negated by Mystical Beasts monsters from Pendulum decks, it's also a spell card so it will allow us to triger the full power effect of Sky Striker cards more easilly. Sky Striker Maneuver - Afterburners is an alternative way to handle monsters and is a safe way to break through monsters that prevent special summons like Vanity Fiend or monsters with annoying disruption effects to start our loops, it is searchable by Engage. Fantastical Dragon Phantazmay is a good way to draw cards when going second against decks like Orcust, and can pressure opponent's play that set monsters with disruption effects The artifact package is an excellent option to lock combo decks when going first with Artifact Scythe and can stop Orcust and Thunder Dragon with Artifact Lancea. Lastly Anti-Spell Fragrance is a way to shut down Sky Striker and Pendulum when going first and won't be a problem after we set our board.

deck_name: Just Your Everyday Fairytale | Legend Of Heart
deck_excerpt: Legendary Dragons, Legendary Knights, and weird fusion things
deck_description: TIMEEEEEEEAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAS!!!!!!!!!

Dino's aren't the most competetive deck to play right now but surely are a lot fun. They don't make the most impressive boards but can make some that easily win you the game (They also have a OTK, for those who want). This Dino deck really depends on going second and going first with the wrong cards in your hand can hurt sometimes.  Lost World Dino is one of my favorite decks and I will show you why. Dino's have a very simple strategy; putting big beatsticks and negates on the board. This is mostly possible with ULTIMATE CONDUCTER TYRANNO, the EVOLZAR duo and PANKRATOPS. The main plays start with OVIRAPTOR and a combination of MISCELLANEOUSAURUS and/or LOST WORLD in your hand, this is why you play 3 FOSSIL DIG to search you combo starters. I play 6 handtraps to disrupt opponents plays and 2 to get rid of powerfull boss monsters.  The OTK is having an token on your opponents field with LOST WORLD (OTK is still possible without token, you opponent just needs a monster on their side of the field), getting DUGARES on the board with UCT, activating DUGARES's effect to double UCT's attack, linking DUGARES and another card away for PENTESTAG (that points to UCT), destroy a monster in your hand to change your opponents monsters to face down defense position, attack every monster with UCT for 7000 piercing dmg (and directly after all monsters are gone.  Any questions can be send to me, will do my best to answer them quickly.  Thank you and have fun playing!

deck_excerpt: A Malefic deck with two win conditions
deck_description: This deck has two win conditions. The first one is a standard beatdown focused playstyle with Malefic Stardust/Malefic Territory to protect Malefic world. In ~80% of starting hands you will have either 1 Malefic World or 1 Malefic Territory (terrraforming but better).  The second win condition of this deck is to sit on Mathmech Processor Final Sigma in the extra monster zone with a skill drain on field. To summon Final Sigma all you need is either: Malefic Parallel Gear + Cyber End Dragon OR Malefic Paradox Gear + Malefic World/Malefic Territory. Conbined with Skill Drain, Final Sigma will be extremely hard to out for the opponent (assuming no Kaijus)

deck_excerpt: Traptrix and Mekk-Knights in a deck together
deck_description: The idea behind this deck is to not only give your Mekk-knight monsters some okay going first plays but also to stun out your opponent by using the Trap Hole and Traptrix cards. Any hand that opens with at least 1 Mekk, 1 Traptrix, and 1 spell/trap is capable of creating a somewhat strong opening board.  Going first your best bet is to establish a column by turning any main deck Traptrix monster into Sera and using any spell/trap to create an opening for your Mekk-knights to be summoned. Once you've done most of your Mekk-knight plays, you can either turn any level 4s on the field into a Traptrix Rafflesia or a Time Theif Redoer or using 3 cards to create BLS - Soldier of Chaos. This deck is capable of opening only monsters or only spell/traps, but it is usually a healthy mix of both.  The best hand I've experienced with this deck was:  Myrmeleo, Purple Nightfall, Kagetokage, Shade Brigandine, and Secret.

deck_excerpt: A fun deck combining Arcana Force in the Main Deck with mostly Utopia cards in the Extra Deck.
deck_description: Sometimes you just feel like using certain themes and not try to make it competitive. That's what I did here, using the Arcana Force archetype for the Main Deck, and mostly filling my Extra Deck with Utopia monsters.  Adding Ties of the Brethren, Shining Angel and Nova Summoner for a bit of consistency, this deck is meant to use these Level 4 LIGHT Fairy monsters to Summon the various Utopia forms and hopefully bring victory. With 'Utopia Double' and 'Double or Nothing!' included in the deck, an OTK is possible if the opponent controls an ATK position monster with max 2000 ATK. Honest can help make an OTK, such as this one, easier. Note that Honest cannot be used in conjunction with Utopia the Lightning's effect, as Lightning's ATK change happens after the final chance to activate Honest.

deck_excerpt: My take on an effective Salamangreats deck for the November 2019 format
deck_description: This deck makes use of salamangreats' ability to use multiple hand traps to hinder the opponent while setting up a strong stun to hinder their plays turn 1. Going first you can go 1 of 2 ways: 1) If you know your facing a Nibiru, make Apollousa by 5th summon. You can use will, archiver, and your natural extenders to do this. 2) If you know there's no nibiru, just perform the standard salamangreat combo, you should be able to end on 2 negates on field and at least 1 hand trap in the hand for 3 disruptions. Ghost belle is a very strong hand trap this format, being able to hit every one of the top decks. Orcust- stops cymbal skeleton and Yellow Martin for the LunaLight build. Strikers- Stops raye and kagari. Salamangreats- what doesn't it stop? Thunder- Stops hawk preventing the thunder player from extending combo.     The side deck is more diverse able to handle a wider variety of decks. Red reboot would be your flex spot, if you feel like adding a 3rd twin twisters or another sanctum feel free. You'll notice no nibiru, this is because nibiru isn't really as strong as you'd believe right now. Its a blow-out vs rogue decks but hurts the meta decks very little. If you disagree, you're welcome to experiment with it, I feel its a waste of space better used for more effective hand traps or stun cards like the artifact package. I have included trap trick in the side deck as a 3rd sanctum. The idea behind this is that trap trick is a way to thin 2 cards from your deck upon activation. Even if you open with sanctum and trap trick, you can use the card to grab an impermanence and thin 2 cards from your deck and increase consistency.

deck_excerpt: HERO it's comming... and it's very strong deck.
deck_description:
HERO é um arquétipo de cards do Yu-Gi-Oh! no qual, eu mais amo nesse jogo! Desde Yu-Gi-Oh!GX, quando o Jaden Yuki invocava aquelas lindas fusões clássicas, sempre tive um enorme desejo em fazer esse deck, ao qual, admiro muito. Bem, pra quem não sabe, o deck gira em torno de monstros do tipo guerreiro, dos mais variados atributos, que envolve principalmente invocação do deck extra de monstros fusão, sendo eles definidos nas seguintes tipos de HERO:
  • Herói Elementar
  • Herói do Destino
  • Herói Mascarado
  • Herói da Visão
  • Herói Maléfico
  • Neospacial
  • Herói Xtra
E bem, e a mecânica do deck é até que muito boa, no qual você busca as suas matérias de fusão e pelos mais variados efeitos, busca meios de usa-las para trazer seus HEROS mais fortes. E por muito tempo, o deck foi bem abalado, tendo a carta "Um Herói Vive" limitada, e só recentemente, o Herói do Elemento Stratos saiu completamente da banlist, após quase 5 anos banido/limitada, e claro, o Herói do Destino - Malicioso, que com mais uma cópia, te dá acesso a mais combos e monstros a serem trazidos. O seu campo Core, é sempre passar o turno, se for você quem começa, com um Herói Destino - Plasma, que nega todos os efeitos de monstros de face pra cima no campo do oponente, uma habilidade extremamente forte, forçando seu oponente a ter que interagir com você e gastar recursos, e mais um monstro para se dar a Mudar a Máscara, que vai ser setada e utilizada no turno do oponente, com o objetivo de trazer a Lei Negra, o Herói Mascarado, que todas as cartas do oponente são banidas em vez de ir pro cemitério, e claro, a sua habilidade de que se o oponente adiciona cartas na mão do deck, ele descartar uma carta, o que faz o seu oponente perder ainda mais recursos. Também pode se por um Herói do Destino - Distopia sendo apontado pelo Herói Xtra Dizimador Horrífico, que aumenta o atk dele e de monstros HERO em suas zonas em 100 pra cada HERO de nome diferente no cemitério, e claro, Distopia destrói qualquer carta no turno de qualquer jogador, contanto que ele esteja com o atk alterado, o que é sempre bom ter em mãos, o Neos Honesto, para dar muito atk as seus HEROS, servindo tanto para bater no seu oponente, como para defender seus HEROS. E como jogando por segundo, fazendo os mais variados combos para trazer o Herói Elementar Sunriser que te dá acesso à Fusão Miraculosa, podendo assim trazer o Herói Elementar Zero Absoluto usando o Herói Elementar Liquidman e outro Herói Elementar, para se dar uma Mudar a Máscara no Zero Absoluto, com o objetivo de "triggar" os efeitos do Zero Absoluto e o Herói Mascarado Acid,  que, quando Zero Absoluto saí do campo ele destrói todos os monstros do oponente, "trigga" o efeito do Acid, que quando entra no campo, destrói todas as cartas mágicas e armadilhas do oponente, deixando o campo livre para um OTK, sendo para mim, um dos combos mais fortes dos HEROS. O deck ainda irá receber os futuros suportes, mas o que já se percebe, que o deck de HERO chegou chegando, e vai causar bastante barulho, muito certamente.

deck_excerpt: Heraldry Crest is ready for action!
deck_description: Vetrix, known as Tron in the Japanese and Italian versions and born Byron Arclight, is a character appearing in the Yu-Gi-Oh! ZEXAL anime. He appears as the secondary antagonist during the World Duel Carnival arc. Vetrix was formerly involved with Dr. Faker's business, and has sworn to take revenge alongside his sons: Trey, Quattro and Quinton. After Trey was defeated by Yuma Tsukumo, he made plans to target him as well since he possessed the "Original Number". Though his appearance is that of a child younger than the rest of the Vetrix Family, he is their father. He was betrayed by Dr. Faker, who used him and Kazuma Tsukumo as sacrifices to open the door to another dimension. When he returned, his form was mutated into that of a child. Vetrix plays a "Heraldic" Deck, composed of cards focused on control and manipulation, including the "Heraldic Beasts" and a line-up of "Heraldry" Spell/Trap Cards. His main strategy involves swarm tactics through cards such as "Heraldic Beast Eale" and "Heraldry Reborn" so he can easily Xyz Summon his "Number" monsters. Several of his "Heraldic Beasts" also generate card advantages by banishing themselves from his Graveyard.

deck_name: Prank-Kids Invoked ft. Thunder Dragon November 2019
deck_excerpt: Prank-Kids with multiple Fusions and disruptions.
deck_description:
The main objective of the deck is to get a Colossus or Toadally Awesome for negations/lockdown. Also, it is capable to make Prank-Kids Battle Butler or Invoked Mechaba (if you end up with 1 of 2 main archetypes). A few notes for you:
  • Prank-Kids monsters: To swarm the deck and to have enough resources for Battle Butler. Notes: Prank-Kids Fansies should send Prank-Kids Plan to recycle those Prank-Kids. When you use Prank-Kids Rocksies effect, you should banish those Thunder Dragon cards to get access to Thunder Dragon Fusion (then make Battle Butler with it) or to refresh hand with Thunder Dragonhawk (in case your hand is bad).
  • Prank-Kids Pandemonium should only be used in your last step or your opponent's turn since it locks you in Prank-Kids monsters.
  • Magical Meltdown has better protection to your Fusion monsters, so if you have both Field Spell, activate Magical Meltdown after Prank-Kids Place.
  • If you want to make Invoked Mechaba, you should use either: Ghost Ogre & Snow Rabbit/ Thunder Dragonhawk / opponent monsters in the GY (especially Effect Veiler) or you can make Reprodocus to change the Attribute of monsters it points to LIGHT.
  • Thunder Dragon Fusion is mainly for shuffling back materials for Prank-Kids Battle Butler, so to make Thunder Dragon Colossus, you can banish Thunder Dragonroar to bring out Thunder Dragondark, then send it to the GY (you can do it by linking it with another monster for Reprodocus) to search Thunder Dragon Fusion. You can have Colossus by using Hawk (if you have one) to resurrect Roar then Contact Fusion.
  • Last but not least, by using Prank-Kids Special Summons, you can bring out Toadally Awesome by 2 Prank-Kids Dropsies, adding an extra layer to your disruptions.
Thank you for reading this, and if you have any questions, comment below!
